Author: CiPhEr#2091
Content: This might be a question for @jl777c i'm trying to duplicate the mining calculator here: https://dexstats.info/piratecalc.php and the equation I used to use for finding mining rewards for equihash coins was: ((my_hashrate / (diff*8192)) * 86400) * BlockReward = coins in 24 hours. If I modify the equation to multiplying diff by around 19 I get somewhat close but if difficulty goes substantially up or down it loses precision. After researching, this number that is multiplied by diff is called the 'work size' for the network. Does anyone know the proper work size to be using for this equation?         EDIT: Looks like the calculator on dexstats doesn't even use difficulty. It uses the following equation: (myhashrate/nethash)*((86400/blocktime)*BlockReward).
